						               													<description>This set of twelve battles and ten divisional army lists represent actions which took place at the start of the Great War in 1914. The scenarios are set in Belgium and northern France.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scenarios covered by this book pre-date the trench warfare. The last scenario, White Sheet, has a hint of what was to come, but even here the defenders were not occupying a coherent trench system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a series of scenarios taking place in open countryside. Occasionally defenders are occupying trenches, but usually they are not.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scenarios:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Orsma&amp;euml;l-Gussenhoven, Belgium 10th August 1914&amp;#10;     Haelen, Belgium 12th August 1914&amp;#10;     Tirlemont, Belgium 18th August 1914&amp;#10;     Longlier, Belgian Ardennes 20th August 1914&amp;#10;     Bleid, Belgian Ardennes 22nd August 1914&amp;#10;     Neufch&amp;acirc;teau, Belgian Ardennes 22nd August 1914&amp;#10;     St. Vincent, Belgian Ardennes 22nd August 1914&amp;#10;     Mons &amp;ndash; The Salient, Belgium 23rd August 1914&amp;#10;     Audregnies, Belgium 24th August 1914&amp;#10;     Le Cateau, France 26th August 1914&amp;#10;     N&amp;eacute;ry, France 1st September 1914&amp;#10;     White Sheet, Belgium 1st November 1914&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Army Lists:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Belgian Cavalry Division&amp;#10;     Belgian Infantry Division&amp;#10;     British Cavalry Division&amp;#10;     British Infantry Division&amp;#10;     French Cavalry Division&amp;#10;     French Infantry Division&amp;#10;     French Reserve Infantry Division&amp;#10;     German Cavalry Division&amp;#10;     German Infantry Division&amp;#10;     German Reserve Infantry Division&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash; extracted description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
